#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="pli-tv-bu-vb-np28"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:0.1"
msgid "Theravāda Vinaya"
msgstr "Theravāda Collection on Monastic Law"

#. HTML: </p><p class="division"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:0.2"
msgid "Mahāvibhaṅga"
msgstr "Monks’ rules and their analysis"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:0.3"
msgid "Nissaggiyakaṇḍa"
msgstr "The chapter on relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:0.4"
msgid "Pattavagga"
msgstr "Monks’ Relinquishment"

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:0.5"
msgid "28. Accekacīvarasikkhāpada"
msgstr "28. The training rule on haste-cloth"

#. HTML: </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc1, pts-cs-bu-np28.1, ms1V_2385
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena aññataro mahāmatto pavāsaṃ gacchanto bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—"
msgstr "At that time a government official who was going away sent a message to the monks:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.3"
msgid "“āgacchantu bhadantā vassāvāsikaṃ dassāmī”ti."
msgstr "“Come, Venerables, I wish to give a rainy-season robe.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū—"
msgstr "The monks thought,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.5"
msgid "“vassaṃvuṭṭhānaṃ bhagavatā vassāvāsikaṃ anuññātan”ti,"
msgstr "“The Master has allowed rainy-season robes only for those who have completed the rains residence,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.6"
msgid "kukkuccāyantā nāgamaṃsu."
msgstr "and being afraid of wrongdoing they did not go."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.7"
msgid "Atha kho so mahāmatto ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "That government official complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.8"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhadantā mayā dūte pahite nāgacchissanti."
msgstr "“How can you not come when I send a message?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.9"
msgid "Ahañhi senāya gacchāmi."
msgstr "I’m going out with the army."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.10"
msgid "Dujjānaṃ jīvitaṃ dujjānaṃ maraṇan”ti."
msgstr "It’s hard to know whether I will live or die.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2, ms1V_2386
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.11"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa mahāmattassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa."
msgstr "The monks heard the complaints of that government official,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.12"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "and they told the Master."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "Soon afterwards the Master gave a teaching and addressed the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.1.14"
msgid "“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, accekacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā nikkhipitun”ti."
msgstr "“Monks, I allow you to receive haste-cloth, and then store it.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3, pts-vp-pli3.261, pts-cs-bu-np28.1.2, pts-vp-en2.152, ms1V_2387
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū—"
msgstr "Knowing that the Master had made this allowance,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.2"
msgid "“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ accekacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā nikkhipitun”ti,"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.3"
msgid "accekacīvarāni paṭiggahetvā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmenti."
msgstr "monks received haste-cloth"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.4"
msgid "Tāni cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhanti."
msgstr "and stored them beyond the robe season, in bundles on a bamboo robe-rack."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: Addasa → addasā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.5"
msgid "Addasa kho āyasmā ānando senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto tāni cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhante disvā bhikkhū etadavoca—"
msgstr "While walking about the dwellings, Venerable Ānanda saw that cloth, and he asked the monks,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.6"
msgid "“kassimāni, āvuso, cīvarāni cīvaravaṃse bhaṇḍikābaddhāni tiṭṭhantī”ti?"
msgstr "“Whose cloth is this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.7"
msgid "“Amhākaṃ, āvuso, accekacīvarānī”ti."
msgstr "“It’s our haste-cloth.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.8"
msgid "“Kīvaciraṃ panāvuso, imāni cīvarāni nikkhittānī”ti?"
msgstr "“How long have you stored it?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.9"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmato ānandassa yathānikkhittaṃ ārocesuṃ."
msgstr "They told him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.10"
msgid "Āyasmā ānando ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—"
msgstr "and Ānanda then complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.11"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū accekacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmessantī”ti."
msgstr "“How can these monks receive haste-cloth and then store it beyond the robe season?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4, ms1V_2388
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.12"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando te bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi … pe …—"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, Ānanda told the Master. …"

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.153
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.13"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū accekacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmentī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks do this?”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.14"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.15"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.16"
msgid "kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā accekacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetvā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmessanti."
msgstr "Monks, how can those foolish men receive haste-cloth and then store it beyond the robe season?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.17"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.18"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.18a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="rule"> 
#. VAR: kattikatemāsikapuṇṇamaṃ → kat­ti­ka­te­māsi­puṇṇamaṃ (s1-3)
#. REF: sc5, ms1V_2389
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.19"
msgid "“Dasāhānāgataṃ kattikatemāsikapuṇṇamaṃ bhikkhuno paneva accekacīvaraṃ uppajjeyya, accekaṃ maññamānena bhikkhunā paṭiggahetabbaṃ,"
msgstr "‘When there are ten days left to the Kattika full moon that ends the first rains residence and haste-cloth is given to a monk,"

#. VAR: yāva cīvarakālasamayaṃ → yāvacīvara … (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.20"
msgid "paṭiggahetvā yāva cīvarakālasamayaṃ nikkhipitabbaṃ."
msgstr "he may receive it if he regards it as urgent."

#. VAR: uttari → uttariṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:1.2.21"
msgid "Tato ce uttari nikkhipeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "If he stores it beyond that, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. HTML: </h2><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc6, pts-cs-bu-np28.2, ms1V_2390
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.1"
msgid "Dasāhānāgatanti"
msgstr "There are ten days left:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.2"
msgid "dasāhānāgatāya pavāraṇāya."
msgstr "the invitation ceremony is ten days in the future."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc7, ms1V_2391
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.3"
msgid "Kattikatemāsikapuṇṇamanti"
msgstr "The Kattika full moon that ends the first rains residence:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.4"
msgid "pavāraṇā kattikā vuccati."
msgstr "the Kattika full moon of the invitation ceremony is what is meant."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc8, ms1V_2392
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.5"
msgid "Accekacīvaraṃ nāma"
msgstr "Haste-cloth:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss">
#. REF: pts-vp-en2.154
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.6"
msgid "senāya vā gantukāmo hoti, pavāsaṃ vā gantukāmo hoti, gilāno vā hoti, gabbhinī vā hoti, assaddhassa vā saddhā uppannā hoti, appasannassa vā pasādo uppanno hoti,"
msgstr "when someone wants to go out with the army, when someone wants to go away, when someone is sick, when someone is pregnant, when someone without faith acquires faith, when someone without confidence acquires confidence—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.7"
msgid "so ce bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pahiṇeyya—"
msgstr "if that person sends a message to the monks, saying,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.8"
msgid "“āgacchantu bhadantā vassāvāsikaṃ dassāmī”ti,"
msgstr "“Come, Venerables, I wish to give rains-residence cloth,”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.9"
msgid "etaṃ accekacīvaraṃ nāma."
msgstr "this is called “haste-cloth.”"

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc9, ms1V_2393
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.10"
msgid "Accekaṃ maññamānena bhikkhunā paṭiggahetabbaṃ"
msgstr "He may receive it if he regards it as urgent."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.11"
msgid "paṭiggahetvā yāva cīvarakālasamayaṃ nikkhipitabbanti"
msgstr "He may then store it until the end of the robe season:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.12"
msgid "saññāṇaṃ katvā nikkhipitabbaṃ—“idaṃ accekacīvaran”ti."
msgstr "establishing the perception of it as a haste-cloth, he may store it."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc10, ms1V_2394
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.13"
msgid "Cīvarakālasamayo nāma"
msgstr "The robe season:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.14"
msgid "anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso,"
msgstr "for one who has not done the robe-making ceremony, it is the last month of the rainy season;"

# NOTE: That is, the last month of the rainy season, plus the four months of the cold season.
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.15"
msgid "atthate kathine pañcamāsā."
msgstr "for one who has done the robe-making ceremony, it is the five month period."

#. HTML: </span></p><p><span class="term"> 
#. REF: sc11, pts-vp-pli3.262, ms1V_2395
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.16"
msgid "Tato ce uttari nikkhipeyyāti"
msgstr "If he stores it beyond that:"

#. HTML: </span><span class="gloss"> 
#. VAR: nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ → nissaggiyaṃ hoti (s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.17"
msgid "anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimaṃ divasaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "for one who has not done the robe-making ceremony, if he goes beyond the last day of the rainy season, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

# NOTE: The robe-making season ends if the Sangha decides to forgo the robe-making privilege, or if the monk leaves the monastery where he spent the rains residence and gives up any intention of making a robe before the end of the cold season, see [](MS.1.1869) and [](Mv.7.13.2).
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.18"
msgid "Atthate kathine kathinuddhāradivasaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "For one who has done the robe-making ceremony, if he goes beyond the day on which the robe-making season ends, the cloth becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. HTML: </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.19"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The cloth should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. HTML: <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.20"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. HTML: <span class="pe"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.21"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in [Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17](pli-tv-bu-vb-np1#13), with appropriate substitutions. "

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.22"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, accekacīvaraṃ cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this haste-cloth which I have kept beyond the robe season is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.23"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.24"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.25"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.26"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this cloth back to you.’”"

#. HTML: </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.26a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc12, ms1V_2396
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.27"
msgid "Accekacīvare accekacīvarasaññī cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is haste-cloth and he perceives it as haste-cloth, and he keeps it beyond the robe season, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.28"
msgid "Accekacīvare vematiko cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is haste-cloth, but he is unsure if it is, and he keeps it beyond the robe season, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. REF: pts-vp-en2.155
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.29"
msgid "Accekacīvare anaccekacīvarasaññī cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it is haste-cloth, but he does not perceives it as haste-cloth, and he keeps it beyond the robe season, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.30"
msgid "Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññī … pe …"
msgstr "If it has not been determined, but he perceives it as determined …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.31"
msgid "avikappite vikappitasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been transferred, but he perceives it as transferred …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.32"
msgid "avissajjite vissajjitasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been given away, but he perceives it as given away …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.33"
msgid "anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been lost, but he perceives it as lost …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.34"
msgid "avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been destroyed, but he perceives it as destroyed …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.35"
msgid "adaḍḍhe daḍḍhasaññī …"
msgstr "If it has not been burnt, but he perceives it as burnt …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.36"
msgid "avilutte viluttasaññī cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If it has not been stolen, but he perceives it as stolen, and he keeps it beyond the robe season, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. HTML: </p><p><span class="rule"> 
#. REF: sc13, ms1V_2397
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.37"
msgid "Nissaggiyaṃ cīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he uses a cloth which should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. HTML: </span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.38"
msgid "Anaccekacīvare accekacīvarasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not haste-cloth, but he perceives it as haste-cloth, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.39"
msgid "Anaccekacīvare vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If it is not haste-cloth, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.40"
msgid "Anaccekacīvare anaccekacīvarasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr "If it is not haste-cloth and he does not perceive it as haste-cloth, there is no offense."

#. HTML: </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.40a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. HTML: </h2><p>
#. REF: sc14, ms1V_2398
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.41"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

#. VAR: antosamaye → antosamayaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.42"
msgid "antosamaye adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, ḍayhati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,"
msgstr "if within the robe season the haste-cloth is determined, transferred, given away, lost, destroyed, burnt, stolen, or taken on trust;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.43"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.44"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. HTML: </p><hr><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc15, ms1V_2399
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-np28:2.45"
msgid "Accekacīvarasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The eighth rule, the training rule on haste-cloth, is finished."
